    <stitle>FRAME - GENERAL FRAME RECOMMENDATIONS - REINFORCEMENT TO INCREASE CAPACITY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="0">
        <title>REINFORCEMENT TO INCREASE CAPACITY</title>
        <para>Reinforcement of the chassis frame to support either additional loading or concentrated loading does not
            increase vehicle load carrying capacity unless it has been fully verified that all other vehicle components,
            such as the brake system, steering system, suspension system, etc. can properly and safely support the
            increased loading.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
